# <type>(<scope>): <description>   ← subject: ≤72 chars, imperative, present tense
#   type: feat|fix|refactor|docs|test|chore|perf|ci
#   (enforced by commit-subject-length and commit-subject-format hooks)
#
# <blank line>
# WHY is this change needed? Write so any reader — future-self, collaborators,
# AI agents, CI tooling — can understand the purpose in isolation.
# Explain the problem, constraint, or decision. Not the mechanics.
# Wrap lines at ~72 chars.
# (enforced by commit-body-required hook)
#
# Refs: https://github.com/users/noordeep12/projects/1
# (or Refs: #<issue-number>)
# (enforced by commit-refs-footer hook)
#
# Enable this template locally:  git config commit.template .gitmessage
